This paper proposes a new approach for classification and regression using prototypes on hyperspherical output spaces. The paper focuses on machine learning and neural networks, which are typically covered in the computer science categories of arXiv. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper introduces a new approach for classification and regression using prototypes, which is a common topic in machine learning research. The second likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper discusses experiments on image classification datasets. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper proposes a new approach for machine learning tasks. The fourth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper focuses on neural networks. The fifth likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), as the paper discusses incorporating class semantics into the optimization process.
